us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFrameTuple3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FrameTuple3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFramePoint3DBasics, FixedFrameVector3DBasics, FramePoint3DBasics, FrameTuple3DBasics, FrameVector3DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePoint3D, FrameVector3D

    public interface FixedFrameTuple3DBasics
extends FrameTuple3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DBasics
    FixedFrameTuple3DBasics is the base implementation for FramePoint3D and FrameVector3D.

    In addition to representing a Tuple3DBasics, a constant ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFrameTuple3DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on tuples occur in the same coordinate system.

    When using this interface, the reference frame of this tuple is assumed to be immutable, i.e. the tuple is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    Because a FixedFrameTuple3DBasics extends Tuple3DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Tuple3DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFrameTuple3DBasics.

        default void setMatchingFrame(FrameTuple2DReadOnly frameTuple2DReadOnly,
                              double z)
        Sets the x and y components of this frame tuple with the x and y components of the given frameTuple2DReadOnly and the z-component to the given z.

        If other is expressed in the frame as this, then this method is equivalent to set(FrameTuple2DReadOnly, double).

        If other is expressed in a different frame than this, then this is set with frameTuple2DReadOnly and z, and then transformed to be expressed in this.getReferenceFrame().

        Parameters:
        frameTuple2DReadOnly - the frame tuple to copy the values from. Not modified.
        z - the new z-coordinate for this tuple.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(FrameTuple3DReadOnly other,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from this frame tuple to other given the percentage alpha.

        this = (1.0 - alpha) * this + alpha * other

        Parameters:
        other - the other frame tuple used for the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage used for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in not modifying this frame tuple, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this frame tuple to other.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(FrameTuple3DReadOnly frameTuple1,
                         FrameTuple3DReadOnly frameTuple2,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from frameTuple1 to frameTuple2 given the percentage alpha.

        this = (1.0 - alpha) * frameTuple1 + alpha * frameTuple2

        Parameters:
        frameTuple1 - the first frame tuple used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        frameTuple2 - the second frame tuple used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage to use for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in setting this frame tuple to frameTuple1, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this frame tuple to frameTuple2.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if either frameTuple1 or frameTuple2 is not expressed in the same frame as this.
